# MATLAB (this machine)

MATLAB is installed but **not** on the default shell `PATH`. Use the full path below.

| Item | Path |
|------|------|
| Install root | `/Applications/MATLAB_R2025b.app` |
| Executable | `/Applications/MATLAB_R2025b.app/bin/matlab` |
| Version | R2025b (25.2) |

## Running scripts

Prefer **batch** mode (non-interactive, exits when done):

```bash
/Applications/MATLAB_R2025b.app/bin/matlab -batch "cd('path/to/script/dir'); run('script_name.m')"
```

Or from the script directory:

```bash
cd /path/to/script/dir
/Applications/MATLAB_R2025b.app/bin/matlab -batch "run('script_name.m')"
```

Do not assume `matlab` or `which matlab` works unless `PATH` has been set in that shell session.

